    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1878-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1878-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <head>No. 489.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Consulate at Tunis</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-11-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 26, 1878</date>. (Received, December
                                13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 15.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose to the State Department copy of
                            a communication to his excellency the prime minister and minister of
                            foreign affairs, embracing the views of the State and Treasury
                            Departments of the United States Government on the subject of a tax
                            proposed to be levied by this government for the maintenance (in part)
                            of light-houses on the coast. The communication embraces the views of
                            the Secretary of State, based on a letter from Rear-Admiral John
                            Rodgers, chairman of Light-House Board, and Hon. John B. Hawley, Acting
                            Secretary of the Treasury, all referred to in letter of the Hon. William
                            M. Evarts, dated October 23, 1878.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. W. FISH,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States Consul,
                                    Tunis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
